The paper discusses the lack of rigor in the engineering of modern network infrastructure and the need for formal methods to improve the architecture and abstractions. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper discusses the application of formal methods to specification, verification, and synthesis of networking protocols and applications, which could also place it in the sub-categories of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), Programming Languages (cs.PL), Software Engineering (cs.SE), and Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO).
